- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper analyzes the time complexity of the algorithm and compares it to other known solutions. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial objects (runs) over a general ordered alphabet. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with strings and their properties (runs) over a general ordered alphabet. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the information content of a string and how to efficiently compute its runs.
